title: Woman's sister reveals to her about her infidelity, woman then tells brother-in-law about the affair: 'I couldn’t just sit back and watch Tom live a lie'
description: We've all kept secrets for our siblings. Whether that be covering for them when they sneak out of the house or fixing mom's broken vase before she gets home so no one gets in trouble; sibling solidarity is one of the firmest bonds we can have. That said, we've also all tattled on a sibling in a moment of weakness. Younger siblings are known to be the bigger tattlers since they remain in the light of our parent's affection for much longer. It's always an advantage to be the baby of the family, even if you're stuck at home the longest while everyone else gets to leave.Once we reach adulthood, the instinct to tattle on our siblings mostly washes away. Sibling solidarity, however, remains forever. I know I would help my sister with anything, no questions asked. However, there are some things in life that are hard to forgive. One woman is in a tough position with her sister after her sister confides in her about her infidelity. She comes to Reddit to ask for advice after she reveals the family secret. Would you have spilled in this situation? Or is this a subject that's better left to the parties involved to deal with?
author: Baiz Hoen

title: 'She gave me two options and one option is never happening': Man's new wife wants to adopt his daughter so ex-wife can no longer be in the picture, man says he'd rather divorce her than force his daughter into adoption
description: If you get to the point in a relationship where you're forced to give your partner an ultimatum, you might as well throw in the towel right then and there. It shouldn't have to be a completely life-changing decision to get what you need, and if you aren't getting what you need, you should probably just get up and go! Sure, the pressure of an ultimatum could help you achieve happiness faster, but couldn't you flip a coin, too? Makes a pros and cons list? Maybe this is an unpopular opinion to have, but ultimatums feel like the option for people who haven't made a single decision for themselves in their lives.There are situations, too, that are too delicate for people to be throwing ultimatums around. Take this man, for example, whose wife made him the ultimatum of either adopting his daughter so his ex-wife and mother of his child stay out of their lives for good or getting a divorce. Honey, if you were that pressed about an ex being involved, you should've thought about that before you married a man with a kid! But I digress… why don't you read their story and make your opinion on ultimatums, et. al.
author: Baiz Hoen

title: 21 Fantasy Feline Memes Catching Cat Comedy and Toss it Your Way Like a Coin to the Witcher
description: Hello, geeky cat pawrents! How was your weekly D&D session? Did your cat run over the miniatures on the map to become the new BBEG of the campaign? And how about that board game night you have been planning for months? Did your cat eat the dice again…? Besides a recommendation to have a vet check-up at this point, for us it sounds about right - every geeky cat pawrent deals with these situations. But what can we do? We love our cat dearly, but also Balthazor, our level 14 orc warlock that we play with our group of D&D friends. He also has a cat familiar.But, you know? There are plenty of wholesome moments that involve a geeky lifestyle with cat pawrenting. You probably experienced cozying up in a favorite spot with a favorite book, and your cat comes up to snuggle on your lap. Or you make a geeky movie night with friends, and your cat comes to you all to make biscuits on the couch. These are some of our favorite feline moments, truly.
author: Ayala Sorotsky

title: 'I walked right out with the first one put in my arms': Cat mom saves smol Siamese kitten from kitten mill while on vacation, immediately adopts her into their wholesome feline family
description: We hope you're having a sweet, slow Sunday, feline fam. We are currently snuggled up on our couch, surrounded by blankets and fluffy felines, wishing we were somewhere warmer (with our cats, of course). Doesn't a vacation sound just purrfect right now? Some nice, tropical beach or a city where it's above freezing will do. Actually, we'll go anywhere where we're not 2-feet-deep in snow. If we have the chance to encounter the cat distribution system, even better. It's important to always be prepurred to welcome a new kitty into your life. Even when you're on vacation. When you see a cat in need, you don't think, you just do. And that's exactly what this loving cat mom did! She found a Siamese kitten in a kitten mill and immediately scooped her up and adopted her. They traveled back to the US together, and now they're one big, fluffy feline family. She got a trip to Mexico and cute cat? We're just a little bit jealous. Okay, more than a little bit. Scroll down to read the full story below!

title: Error'd: Office Politics
description: "Math is hard, especially timely math," explains The Beast in Black.   Cinephile Jono enjoys contemporary dramas far more than sci-fi. "Letterboxd tells me I've logged this movie 3 times, I'm not sure I'll be watching it in 2566." I hope you are, Jono.   Pieter may have to turn in his official pedants card. Pieter is concerned about the apparent contradiction between the two salaries on offer here, declaring: "The title says She can earn up to 8.000 euro/month. But by the time you get to the actual article link, that amount deflated to 6.000 euro/month. I didn't know it was that bad in the euro zone! Or is it good, since we've got inflation under control? I don't know which way is up anymore..."Pieter, 6,000 is "up to" 8,000. Technically.   Cross-country runner Andrei looks to be taking the long way around for this trip. Says he, "According to Google Maps, one of my transfers involves teleporting about 70 km away to catch my next train."   Finally David B. reports "My wife works as a quality auditor for Initech [ed: the William Lumberg company, presumably, not the Flavor and Fragrance company]. When setting up contact information for a company she will be auditing in the near future they needed some basic information. So much for gender equality." title: Study Finds Peeing Contagious In Chimpanzees
